";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=443706\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:573:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WPForms 1.5.2 is here! There are some new features in this release that pack a big punch and will make using WPForms even easier. Your form fields are about to get a lot smarter so you can get higher quality leads. Plus, Checkbox fields are going to make it even [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/\">Introducing WPForms 1.5.2 &#8211; NEW Checkbox Limits + Smart Email &#038; Phone Fields</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7934:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WPForms 1.5.2 is here!</p>\n<p>There are some new features in this release that pack a big punch and will make using WPForms even easier.</p>\n<p>Your form fields are about to get a lot smarter so you can get higher quality leads. Plus, Checkbox fields are going to make it even easier to segment and convert visitors into paying customers.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s what&#8217;s new in WPForms 1.5.2.</p>\n<h3>Phone Fields Now Auto-Detect Country Codes</h3>\n<p>The Phone field in your forms just got a super helpful revamp.</p>\n<p>The new Smart Phone feature auto-detects your user&#8217;s region as the form is loading. The Phone field will now show which region the person filling out the form is currently located in.</p>\n<p>If a user starts to type in a phone number format that&#8217;s different from the auto-detected format, a message will appear.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443888\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-message-wrong-format.jpg\" alt=\"form-message-wrong-format\" width=\"562\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-message-wrong-format.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-message-wrong-format-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /><br />\nAnd, it&#8217;s really easy for the user to change the auto-detected region on the Phone field.</p>\n<p>For example, say someone from India is visiting the US. The form will auto-detect that they are in the US and add the US phone number format to the Phone field.</p>\n<p>But, let&#8217;s also say that the user wants to enter their phone number which is from India, not the US.</p>\n<p>To do this, they can simply select a different region from the dropdown menu inside the Phone field.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443880\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dropdown-region-select.jpg\" alt=\"dropdown-region-select\" width=\"562\" height=\"301\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dropdown-region-select.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dropdown-region-select-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>If your business gets form entries from multiple regions, you&#8217;ll especially love this Smart Phone feature. We also created this new feature so that international users can now get validation when entering their number, not just US users.</p>\n<p>The Smart Phone feature will help you manage your form entries and keep phone numbers consistent and accurate. And, you&#8217;ll end up with higher quality leads.</p>\n<p>Head over to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-choose-the-right-form-field-for-your-forms/#phone\">how to choose the right form field for your forms</a> to learn more about the different phone formats.</p>\n<h3>Get More Leads With Email Address Typo Detection</h3>\n<p>The Email Field now has an exciting new feature you&#8217;ll love.</p>\n<p>The Smart Email feature spots typos in common domain names. The Email field will now display a message suggesting a fix if a user types in their email address wrong.</p>\n<p>For example, if someone types in liz@gmaill.com or liz@gnail.com, they&#8217;ll see a message with a suggestion of the proper spelling. They can click on the suggestion and the email address will be automatically fixed.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443895\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/smart-email-feature.jpg\" alt=\"smart-email-feature\" width=\"562\" height=\"311\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/smart-email-feature.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/smart-email-feature-300x166.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /><br />\nThe Smart Email feature works with 30 popular email service domains.</p>\n<p>We created the Smart Email feature because we know how important <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/beginners-guide-to-email-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">email marketing</a> is to small business owners and website builders.</p>\n<p>Because of this, we wanted to help make the form entries you receive as accurate as possible. That way, you can focus on building your email list, not fixing it.</p>\n<p>The Smart Email feature is going to help you capture <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-lead-generation-plugins-to-grow-your-email-list/\">higher quality leads</a>, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/12-tips-to-reduce-bounce-rate-and-boost-your-conversions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">reduce bounces</a>, and get more <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-track-wordpress-form-conversions-step-by-step/\">conversions</a> by spotting common email domain typos right away and helping correct them.</p>\n<h3>Limit the Number of Checkboxes Users Can Select</h3>\n<p>The new Checkbox Total Limits feature lets you limit how many checkboxes users can pick on your form. We&#8217;re really excited about this great new option and think you will be too!</p>\n<p>Before, it was difficult to limit checkbox totals on a form. For instance, say your form had 10 dog breeds listed and you asked people to pick their 3 favorite. Users could&#8217;ve ignored your request and selected all 10 dog breeds!</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s why we made Checkbox Total Limits. It&#8217;s now easier than ever to build and manage different <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/insanely-easy-ways-to-grow-your-email-list-fast-starting-now/\">email lists</a> based on your visitor&#8217;s individual preferences.</p>\n<p>If a user tries to select more checkboxes than your set limit, the form will tell them they&#8217;ve exceeded the number of allowed selections.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443921\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/checkbox-total-limit-message.jpg\" alt=\"checkbox-total-limit-message\" width=\"562\" height=\"453\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/checkbox-total-limit-message.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/checkbox-total-limit-message-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, the form won&#8217;t let them submit until that&#8217;s corrected.</p>\n<p>To set or change the Checkbox Total Limit in your Checkbox Field Options, simply click on Advanced Options and enter your desired numerical limit in the Choice Limit box. For a more in-depth look, check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-limit-the-number-of-checkboxes-selections/\">how to limit the number of checkboxes selections.</a></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443726\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms\" width=\"562\" height=\"516\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms-300x275.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And that covers the newest release!</p>\n<p>We think you&#8217;ll agree that WPForms is smarter and simpler than ever before.</p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for?</p>\n<p>Give the newest version of WPForms a try and let us know what you think about all the new updates.</p>\n<p>As always, thank you for your continued support of WPForms. We look forward to helping you succeed with your website and business.</p>\n<p><em>Lisa and the WPForms team</em></p>\n<p>P.S. Don’t have a WPForms Pro license? <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/pricing/\">Click here to get started today</a> and experience the WPForms difference.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/\">Introducing WPForms 1.5.2 &#8211; NEW Checkbox Limits + Smart Email &#038; Phone Fields</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2